'''Allied Marble & Granite Inc.''' is a private company based in [[Seattle, Washington]] known for its [[US West Coast|West Coast]] residential and commercial manufactured stone product installations.<ref name="BIZ">{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/blog/techflash/2013/08/washingtons-best-workplaces-winners.html |first=Becky|last=Monk |publisher=Business Journal |title=Washington's Best Workplaces winner announced to crowd of 1,200 |date=2013-08-09 |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref><ref name="DJ">{{cite web |url=http://digitaljournal.com/article/347532 |title=Home remodeling industry may rebound in weak economy |date=2013-04-08 |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref><ref name="COC">{{cite web |url=http://www.chamberofcommerce.com/seattle-wa/6194522-allied-marble-inc/ |title=Allied Marble Inc |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref>

==History==
Quang Mai is the owner of Allied Marble and Jimmy Mai serves as the company's executive vice president.<ref name="DJ"/><ref name="COC"/><ref name="BIZ1">{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/print-edition/2013/08/09/washingtons-best-workplaces-gold.html?page=all |first=Becky|last=Monk |publisher=Business Journal |title=Washington's Best Workplaces: Gold Medalist-Small Company Category |date=2013-08-09 |accessdate=2013-09-27}}</ref> The company was founded by Mai's father.   Mai and his brother moved Allied Marble to Seattle in 1982.<ref name="DJ"/>

==Award==
Allied Marble won first place in the small company category of the 2013 [[Washington (state)|Washington]]'s Best Workplaces competition.<ref name="BIZ"/><ref name="BIZ1"/>

